size of neutrino mass: 0.3 eV (sum); six orders of magnitude less than electron, 0.5 MeV

W boson: 10.8% to each of the leptons
Z boson: 3.4% to each of the leptons
tau: 17% to electron or muon, 49% 1 hadron, 15% three hadrons

Pionen: 140 MeV
Pi+: up antidown; 99.99% to mu + nu_mu
Pi0: 1/sqrt(2) (u antiu - d antid); 99% 2 gamma

Kaonen: 500 MeV; up or down + strange (-1/3)

Slide 10: be prepared to explain singlets and triplets of what.  (e.g. in
atomic physics, spin quantum number of two electron states)
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Triplet_state

ECAL: trying to maximize magnetic field --> high Z (radiation length)
HCAL: maximize nuclear interaction --> high nucleon number! (interaction length)

